---
layout: base.njk
permalink: /internship.html
title: Internship
description: Join the EISS as a remote intern under a convention de stage. A placement of up to two months supporting the network's events, including the Annual Conference, open to enrolled students. Applications for the first half of the year are preferred.
navKey: internship
lang: en
alternates:
  en: /internship.html
  fr: /internship.fr.html
  de: /internship.de.html
---
{% from "icons.njk" import icon %}

<header class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow">Join us</span>
    <h1>Internship</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">
      Get involved with the European Initiative for Security Studies. Our internship is a remote
      placement of up to two months, run under a French <em>convention de stage</em>, supporting
      the life of the network &mdash; above all our Annual Conference.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>The placement at a glance</h2>

    <div class="tile-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(16rem, 1fr)); margin-block: var(--space-6);">
      <article class="tile">
        <div class="tile-icon" aria-hidden="true">{{ icon("calendar") }}</div>
        <h3>Up to two months, remote</h3>
        <p>
          A placement of up to two months, carried out entirely remotely. It is unpaid, within the
          limits set by your <em>convention de stage</em>.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <div class="tile-icon" aria-hidden="true">{{ icon("users") }}</div>
        <h3>Supporting our events</h3>
        <p>
          As part of your studies, you assist the team preparing and delivering the initiative's
          events &mdash; first and foremost the Annual Conference.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <div class="tile-icon" aria-hidden="true">{{ icon("graduation-cap") }}</div>
        <h3>For enrolled students</h3>
        <p>
          Open to students who can provide a <em>convention de stage</em> from their French (or
          convention-compatible European) higher-education institution.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="muted" style="max-width: 44rem; margin-top: var(--space-5);">
      French law requires every internship to be part of a course of study, covered by a tripartite
      <em>convention de stage</em> between you, your institution and the EISS. We cannot host an
      internship without one, and it must be signed before the placement begins.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-tight">
  <div class="container">
    <article class="card" style="display: grid; gap: var(--space-5); grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: clamp(var(--space-6), 2vw + 1rem, var(--space-8));">
      <div>
        <div class="featured-eyebrow">How to apply</div>
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">Send us your application</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          Send a CV and a short cover letter to
          <a href="mailto:{{ site.contactEmail }}?subject=Internship%20application">{{ site.contactEmail }}</a>,
          telling us your institution and the dates your <em>convention de stage</em> can cover.
          Applications for the first half of the year (January&ndash;June) are preferred.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:{{ site.contactEmail }}?subject=Internship%20application">
            {{ icon("mail") }} Apply by email
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
